[{"id":"VR803351","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a conducting sphere with charge positive Q and radius uppercase R. A point charge of positive Q is a distance lowercase r to the left of the center of the sphere, and is outside the sphere.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803351.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A point charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase r\"><math alttext=\"lowercase r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> from the center of a conducting sphere of charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> and radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase R less than lowercase r\"><math alttext=\"uppercase R less than lowercase r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>R</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>r</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements about the charge distribution on the sphere is correct?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803351_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> charge is evenly distributed about the surface of the sphere.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a net positive charge on the right half of the sphere.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a net negative charge on the sphere.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a net negative charge on the right half of the sphere.</p>"],"answer":1}]